14 SUMMARY
1155 This bill authorizes the Superintendent of Consumer Credit Protection within the
1166 Department of Professional and Financial Regulation to require registration of certain cash-
1177 dispensing machines through the nationwide mortgage licensing system and registry. In all
1188 cases, whether registration is through the nationwide mortgage licensing system and
1199 registry or otherwise, the bill authorizes the superintendent to establish, by rule,
2200 requirements for registration of certain cash-dispensing machines. The bill provides that
2211 certain cash-dispensing machines may not operate as virtual currency kiosks unless the
2222 virtual currency kiosk operator is licensed as a money transmitter.
